cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.DM 

The paper deals with game theory and modal logic, which are both subfields of computer science. The focus on extensive form games and information sets suggests that the paper belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The use of a dynamic epistemic framework and modal logic also suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also deals with logic and knowledge, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The use of a modal logic to describe players' knowledge and its change during the plays could also place the paper in the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. Finally, the paper deals with the mix-up of two interpretations of game structures, which could place it in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category.
